## 6. Doc Drift Detection

If you notice that:

- A file path {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} called for doesn't exist
- A function name in the implementation differs from the {{ inputs.tdd_md | default("TDD.md") }} signature
- An acceptance criterion in {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} wasn't actually verified by qa
- A risk in {{ inputs.project_md | default("PROJECT.md") }} materialized or was disproved
- The actual implementation pattern differs from the {{ inputs.tdd_md | default("TDD.md") }} design

…do NOT update PRD/TDD/Plan yourself. Instead:

```
1. kanban_comment(content="doc-drift: {{ inputs.plan_md | default('Plan.md') }} §3 Epic 1.4 calls for redaction.py;
   actual landed file is redaction/scanner.py. Either {{ inputs.plan_md | default('Plan.md') }} needs update or
   we missed renaming.")

2. Continue your {{ inputs.tasklist_md | default("TASKLIST.md") }} update (with a note that drift was flagged).

3. The human or {{ project.slug }}-planner picks up the doc-drift comment.
```

This keeps PRD/TDD/Plan as immutable contracts — they only change via deliberate, human-reviewed revisions.

